NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In 3rd seat, Stan has a case for opening 3@C as it is likely the opponents have a major suit fit. So 3@C makes it hard for 4th seat to bid, and your side will not miss game. On the other hand, in 1st and 2nd seat, if your hand meets the rule of 20, open 1 of a suit. |
